The Haversine formula is used to calculate great-circle distances between two geographic coordinates (latitude/longitude) on the Earth's surface. In the Laravel example, it enables efficient distance-based queries in databases (e.g., finding nearby locations). Here’s a snippet for Laravel migrations:
php
$table->string('location')->nullable();
$table->decimal('latitude', 10, 8)->nullable();
$table->decimal('longitude', 11, 8)->nullable();

The formula is implemented in SQL or PHP to compute distances dynamically.
